text: Philipp Rösler (born 24 February 1973) is a Vietnamese-German physician and former politician. He was the minister of Economics and Technology and the Vice Chancellor of Germany from 2011 to 2013 during the Angela Merkel cabinet. ==References== Category:1973 births Category:Living people Category:German doctors Category:Politicians from Lower Saxony Category:Vice Chancellors of Germany Category:Asian diplomats Category:Economy ministers of Germany Category:Health ministers of Germany
